      <hedline>
        <hl1>Gently Tie That Tomato</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By PATRICIA JONAS</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Jonas, Patricia</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>This Week's gardening suggestions, on mulching and staking tomatoes</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Mulch and stake tomatoes for better disease control. Use soft ties, wrapping them loosely in a figure eight around the stake or trellis and the plants.</p>
        <p>Water-soluble synthetic fertilizers deliver a rush of nutrients, and even heavy feeders like roses and tomatoes can get too much. Organic fertilizers reduce the risk of overfeeding and improve soil quality over time.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
